Former Public Enterprise minister, Barbra Hogan, says the African National Congress (ANC) used undue influence to interfere with executive appointments at state-owned enterprises. She is currently testifying at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture in Parktown, Johannesburg. Hogan says the Boards appointed to SOEs and the portfolio ministers were responsible for executive appointments at SOEs, not the ruling party. She says former president Jacob Zuma interfered with her executive responsibilities as a minister. Click link for more: 